WEBVTT

00:09.580 --> 00:19.300
28. Woe to the crown of pride, to the drunkards of Ephraim, whose glorious beauty is a fading

00:19.300 --> 00:24.720
flower, which are on the head of the fat valleys of them that are overcome with wine. Behold,

00:24.720 --> 00:29.660
the Lord hath a mighty and strong one, which as a tempest of hail and a destroying storm,

00:30.000 --> 00:35.520
as a flood of mighty waters overflowing, shall cast down to the earth with the hand. The crown

00:35.520 --> 00:40.140
of pride, the drunkards of Ephraim, shall be trodden under feet, and the glorious beauty which is on

00:40.140 --> 00:45.000
the head of the fat valley shall be a fading flower, and as the hasty fruit before the summer,

00:45.320 --> 00:50.940
which when he that looketh upon it seeth, while it is yet in his hand, he eateth it up. In that

00:50.940 --> 00:56.020
day shall the Lord of hosts be for a crown of glory, and for a diadem of beauty unto the residue

00:56.020 --> 01:01.220
of his people, and for a spirit of judgment to him that sitteth in judgment, and for strength

01:01.220 --> 01:06.400
to them that turn the battle to the gate. But they also have erred through wine, and through

01:06.400 --> 01:10.640
strong drink are out of the way. The priest and the prophet have erred through strong drink,

01:10.840 --> 01:15.400
they are swallowed up of wine, they are out of the way through strong drink, they err in vision,

01:15.720 --> 01:20.660
they stumble in judgment. For all the tables are full of vomit and filthiness, so that there is

01:20.660 --> 01:25.840
no place clean. Whom shall he teach knowledge, and whom shall he make to understand doctrine?

01:26.400 --> 01:31.700
Them that are weaned from the milk and drawn from the breasts. For precept must be upon precept,

01:32.000 --> 01:38.280
precept upon precept, line upon line, line upon line, here a little and there a little. For with

01:38.280 --> 01:43.900
stammering lips and another tongue will he speak to this people. To whom he said, This is the rest

01:43.900 --> 01:49.680
wherewith ye may cause the weary to rest, and this is the refreshing. Yet they would not hear. But the

01:49.680 --> 01:54.960
word of the Lord was unto them, precept upon precept, precept upon precept, line upon line,

01:55.300 --> 02:01.040
line upon line, here a little and there a little, that they might go and fall backward, and be broken

02:01.040 --> 02:06.420
and snared and taken. Wherefore hear the word of the Lord, ye scornful men, that rule this people

02:06.420 --> 02:11.540
which is in Jerusalem. Because ye have said, We have made a covenant with death, and with hell

02:11.540 --> 02:16.500
we are at agreement. When the overflowing scourge shall pass through, it shall not come unto us.

02:16.500 --> 02:22.220
For we have made lies our refuge, and under falsehood we have hid ourselves. Therefore thus saith the

02:22.220 --> 02:28.580
Lord God, Behold, I lay in Zion for a foundation, a stone, a tried stone, a precious cornerstone,

02:28.900 --> 02:34.540
a sure foundation. He that believeth shall not make haste. Judgment also will I lay to the line,

02:34.940 --> 02:39.680
and righteousness to the plummet. And the hail shall sweep away the refuge of lies, and the

02:39.680 --> 02:44.700
waters shall overflow the hiding place. And your covenant with death shall be disannulled,

02:44.700 --> 02:49.620
and your agreement with hell shall not stand. When the overflowing scourge shall pass through,

02:49.920 --> 02:54.720
then ye shall be trodden down by it. From the time that it goeth forth, it shall take you. For

02:54.720 --> 02:59.680
morning by morning shall it pass over, by day and by night. And it shall be a vexation only to

02:59.680 --> 03:04.300
understand the report. For the bed is shorter than that a man can stretch himself on it,

03:04.380 --> 03:08.880
and the covering narrower than that he can wrap himself in it. For the Lord shall rise up,

03:09.060 --> 03:13.920
as in Mount Perazim. He shall be wroth as in the valley of Gibeon, that he may do his work,

03:13.920 --> 03:19.900
his strange work, and bring to pass his act, his strange act. Now therefore be ye not mockers,

03:20.020 --> 03:24.200
lest your bands be made strong. For I have heard from the Lord God of hosts a consumption,

03:24.560 --> 03:29.400
even determined upon the whole earth. Give ye ear, and hear my voice. Harken, and hear my speech.

03:29.660 --> 03:35.180
Doth the ploughman plough all day to sow? Doth he open and break the clods of his ground? When he

03:35.180 --> 03:39.860
hath made plain the face thereof, doth he not cast abroad the fitches, and scatter the cumin,

03:39.860 --> 03:44.200
and cast in the principal wheat, and in the appointed barley, and the rye in their place?

03:44.380 --> 03:48.900
For his God doth instruct him to discretion, and doth teach him. For the fitches are not threshed

03:48.900 --> 03:53.340
with a threshing instrument, neither is the cart wheel turned about upon the common. But the

03:53.340 --> 03:57.860
fitches are beaten out with a staff, and the common with a rod. Breadcorn is bruised, because

03:57.860 --> 04:01.940
he will not ever be threshing it, nor break it with the wheel of his cart, nor bruise it with

04:01.940 --> 04:06.500
his horsemen. This also cometh forth from the Lord of hosts, which is wonderful in counsel,

04:06.500 --> 04:10.620
and excellent in working. Isaiah chapter 29.

04:11.260 --> 04:17.740
Woe to Ariel, to Ariel the city where David dwelt! Add ye year to year, let them kill sacrifices.

04:18.240 --> 04:23.100
Yet I will distress Ariel, and there shall be heaviness and sorrow, and it shall be unto me as

04:23.100 --> 04:28.060
Ariel. And I will camp against thee round about, and will lay siege against thee with a mount,

04:28.160 --> 04:32.300
and I will raise forts against thee. And thou shalt be brought down, and thou shalt speak out

04:32.300 --> 04:37.360
the ground, and thy speech shall be low out of the dust, and thy voice shall be as of one that

04:37.360 --> 04:41.760
hath a familiar spirit out of the ground, and thy speech shall whisper out of the dust.

04:42.400 --> 04:46.800
Moreover, the multitude of thy strangers shall be like small dust, and the multitude of the

04:46.800 --> 04:52.120
terrible ones shall be as chuff that passeth away. Yea, it shall be at an instant suddenly.

04:52.460 --> 04:56.940
Thou shalt be visited of the Lord of hosts with thunder, and with earthquake, and great noise,

04:56.940 --> 05:02.680
with storm and tempest, and the flame of devouring fire. And the multitude of all the nations that

05:02.680 --> 05:07.500
fight against Ariel, even all that fight against her and her munition, and that distress her,

05:07.720 --> 05:12.960
shall be as a dream of a night vision. It shall even be as when a hungry man dreameth, and behold

05:12.960 --> 05:18.540
he eateth, but he awakeeth, and his soul is empty. Or as when a thirsty man dreameth, and behold he

05:18.540 --> 05:24.280
drinketh, but he awakeeth, and behold he is faint, and his soul hath appetite. So shall the multitude

05:24.280 --> 05:29.920
of all the nations be that fight against Mount Zion. Stay yourselves and wonder. Cry ye out,

05:30.040 --> 05:35.180
and cry, They are drunken, but not with wine. They stagger, but not with strong drink. For the Lord

05:35.180 --> 05:40.460
hath poured out upon you the spirit of deep sleep, and hath closed your eyes. The prophets and your

05:40.460 --> 05:45.480
rulers, the seers, hath he covered. And the vision of all is become unto you as the words of a book

05:45.480 --> 05:50.560
that is sealed, which men deliver to one that is learned, saying, Read this, I pray thee. And he

05:50.560 --> 05:55.120
saith, I cannot, for it is sealed. And the book is delivered to him that is not learned, saying,

05:55.160 --> 05:59.880
Read this, I pray thee. And he saith, I am not learned. For as much as this people draw near me

05:59.880 --> 06:04.120
with their mouth, and with their lips do honour me, but have removed their heart far from me,

06:04.360 --> 06:09.860
and their fear toward me is taught by the precept of men. Therefore, behold, I will proceed to do a

06:09.860 --> 06:15.240
marvellous work among this people, even a marvellous work and a wonder. For the wisdom of their wise

06:15.240 --> 06:20.160
men shall perish, and the understanding of their prudent men shall be hid. Woe unto them that seek

06:20.160 --> 06:24.700
deep to hide their counsel from the Lord, and their works are in the dark, and they say, Who

06:24.700 --> 06:30.000
seeth us, and who knoweth us? Surely your turning of things upside down shall be esteemed as the

06:30.000 --> 06:35.740
potter's clay. For shall the work say of him that made it, He made me not? Or shall the thing framed

06:35.740 --> 06:41.540
say of him that framed it, He had no understanding. Is it not yet a very little while, and Lebanon shall

06:41.540 --> 06:49.920
be turned into a fruitful field, and the fruitful field shall be esteemed as a forest? And in that

06:49.920 --> 06:55.400
shall see out of obscurity and out of darkness. The meek also shall increase their joy in the Lord,

06:55.760 --> 07:00.420
and the poor among men shall rejoice in the Holy One of Israel. For the terrible one is brought

07:00.420 --> 07:06.100
to nought, and the scorner is consumed, and all that watch for iniquity are cut off. That make a

07:06.100 --> 07:10.600
man an offender for a word, and lay a snare for him that reproveeth in the gate, and turn aside

07:10.600 --> 07:15.480
the just for a thing of nought. Therefore thus saith the Lord who redeemed Abraham concerning the

07:15.480 --> 07:21.800
Jacob. Jacob shall not now be ashamed, neither shall his face now wax pale. But when he seeth

07:21.800 --> 07:27.160
his children, the work of mine hands in the midst of him, they shall sanctify my name, and sanctify

07:27.160 --> 07:32.640
the Holy One of Jacob, and shall fear the God of Israel. They also that erred in spirit shall come

07:32.640 --> 07:38.980
to understanding, and they that murmured shall learn doctrine. Isaiah chapter 30. Woe to the

07:38.980 --> 07:43.620
rebellious children, saith the Lord, that take counsel but not of me, and that cover with the

07:43.620 --> 07:48.800
covering, but not of my spirit, that they may add sin to sin, that walk to go down into Egypt,

07:48.920 --> 07:53.560
and have not asked at my mouth, to strengthen themselves in the strength of Pharaoh, and to

07:53.560 --> 07:58.660
trust in the shadow of Egypt. Therefore shall the strength of Pharaoh be your shame, and the trust

07:58.660 --> 08:03.780
in the shadow of Egypt your confusion. For his princes were at Zohan, and his ambassadors came

08:03.780 --> 08:08.960
to Hainis. They were all ashamed for people that could not profit them, nor be in help nor profit,

08:08.960 --> 08:14.280
but a shame, and also a reproach. The burden of the beasts of the south, into the land of trouble

08:14.280 --> 08:19.620
and anguish, from whence came the young and old lion, the viper and fiery flying serpent. They will

08:19.620 --> 08:23.700
carry their riches upon the shoulders of young asses, and their treasures upon the bunches of

08:23.700 --> 08:28.240
camels, to a people that shall not profit them. For the Egyptians shall help in vain, and to no

08:28.240 --> 08:34.540
purpose. Therefore have I cried concerning this. Their strength is to sit still. Now go, write it

08:34.540 --> 08:39.240
for them in a table, and note it in a book, that it may be for the time to come forever and ever,

08:39.340 --> 08:44.000
that this is a rebellious people, lying children, children that will not hear the law of the Lord,

08:44.440 --> 08:49.420
which say to the seers, see not, and to the prophets, prophesy not unto us right things,

08:49.680 --> 08:55.400
speak unto us smooth things, prophesy deceits, get you out of the way, turn aside out of the path,

08:55.480 --> 09:00.620
cause the Holy One of Israel to cease from before us. Wherefore thus saith the Holy One of Israel,

09:00.620 --> 09:05.140
because you despise this word, and trust in oppression and perverseness, and stay thereon,

09:05.560 --> 09:10.440
therefore this iniquity shall be to you as a breach ready to fall, swelling out in a high wall,

09:10.740 --> 09:15.940
whose breaking cometh suddenly at an instant. And he shall break it as the breaking of the potter's

09:15.940 --> 09:20.760
vessel that is broken in pieces. He shall not spare, so that there shall not be found in the

09:20.760 --> 09:25.140
bursting of it a shard to take fire from the hearth, or to take water withal out of the pit.

09:25.760 --> 09:30.600
For thus saith the Lord God, the Holy One of Israel, in returning and rest shall you be saved.

09:30.620 --> 09:35.960
In quietness and in confidence shall be your strength, and ye would not. But ye said,

09:36.160 --> 09:41.660
No, for we will flee upon horses, therefore shall ye flee. And we will ride upon the swift,

09:42.140 --> 09:46.680
therefore shall they that pursue you be swift. One thousand shall flee at the rebuke of one,

09:47.020 --> 09:51.640
at the rebuke of five shall ye flee, till ye be left as a beacon upon the top of a mountain,

09:51.960 --> 09:57.300
and as an ensign on a hill. And therefore will the Lord wait, that he may be gracious unto you,

09:57.300 --> 10:02.640
and therefore will he be exalted, that he may have mercy upon you. For the Lord is a God of judgment,

10:03.060 --> 10:07.260
blessed are all they that wait for him. For the people shall dwell in Zion at Jerusalem,

10:07.740 --> 10:11.620
thou shalt weep no more, he will be very gracious unto thee at the voice of thy cry.

10:11.980 --> 10:16.280
When he shall hear it, he will answer thee. And though the Lord give you the bread of adversity

10:16.280 --> 10:21.000
and the water of affliction, yet shall not thy textures be removed into a corner any more,

10:21.200 --> 10:25.960
but thine eyes shall see thy textures, and thine ears shall hear a word behind thee, saying,

10:25.960 --> 10:31.200
This is the way, walk ye in it, when ye turn to the right hand and when ye turn to the left.

10:31.900 --> 10:36.660
Ye shall defile also the covering of thy graven images of silver, and the ornament of thy molten

10:36.660 --> 10:42.160
images of gold. Thou shalt cast them away as a menstrous cloth, thou shalt say unto it,

10:42.360 --> 10:47.320
Get thee hence. Then shall he give the rain of thy seed, that thou shalt sow the ground withal,

10:47.680 --> 10:52.020
and bread of the increase of the earth, and it shall be fat and plenteous. In that day shall

10:52.020 --> 10:57.120
thy cattle feed in large pastures. The oxen likewise and the young asses that ear the ground

10:57.120 --> 11:01.200
shall eat clean provender, which hath been winnowed with the shovel and with the fan.

11:01.700 --> 11:06.820
And there shall be upon every high mountain and upon every high hill rivers and streams of water

11:06.820 --> 11:11.880
in the day of the great slaughter when the towers fall. Moreover the light of the moon shall be as

11:11.880 --> 11:16.640
the light of the sun, and the light of the sun shall be sevenfold as the light of seven days,

11:16.900 --> 11:21.300
in the day that the Lord bindeth up the breach of his people and healeth the stroke of their wound.

11:22.160 --> 11:26.780
Behold the name of the Lord cometh from far burning with his anger, and the burden thereof

11:26.780 --> 11:32.840
is heavy. His lips are full of indignation and his tongue as a devouring fire, and his breath as an

11:32.840 --> 11:37.420
overflowing stream shall reach to the midst of the neck to sift the nations with the sieve of

11:37.420 --> 11:43.240
vanity, and there shall be a bridle in the jaws of the people causing them to err. Ye shall have a

11:43.240 --> 11:48.720
song as in the night when a holy solemnity is kept, and gladness of heart as when one goeth with a

11:48.720 --> 11:54.020
pipe to come into the mountain of the Lord to the mighty one of Israel. And the Lord shall cause his

11:54.020 --> 11:58.740
glorious voice to be heard, and shall show the lighting down of his arm with the indignation of

11:58.740 --> 12:04.140
his anger, and with the flame of a devouring fire with scattering and tempest and hailstones.

12:04.860 --> 12:08.920
For through the voice of the Lord shall the Assyrian be beaten down which smote with a rod,

12:09.440 --> 12:13.840
and in every place where the grounded staff shall pass which the Lord shall lay upon him,

12:14.060 --> 12:18.060
it shall be with tablets and harps, and in battles of shaking will he fight with it.

12:18.060 --> 12:23.760
For Tophet is ordained of old, yea, for the king it is prepared, he hath made it deep and large,

12:24.080 --> 12:29.180
the pile thereof is fire and much wood. The breath of the Lord, like a stream of brimstone, doth

12:29.180 --> 12:32.820
kindle it. End of chapters 28 to 30

